<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="sec faq-bg" id="faq">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="ey rv">Questions</div>
    <h2 class="st rv">FREQUENTLY <span class="ac">ASKED</span></h2>
    <div class="faq-wrap">
      <div class="faq-item rv"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">How quickly can you start a new project?</span><div class="faq-toggle">+</div></div><div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-a-inner">For Strike engagements, we can typically start within 2 weeks of a signed agreement. For Build and Embed engagements, 3–4 weeks to ensure the right team composition. We keep a small bench of available engineers specifically to avoid long ramp delays.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item rv d1"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">Do you work with early-stage startups or only enterprises?</span><div class="faq-toggle">+</div></div><div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-a-inner">Both — but with different expectations. We work with pre-seed startups all the way to Fortune 500 enterprises. The engagement model differs: startups typically need us to move fast on MVP builds, while enterprises often need architectural transformation. What we don't do is take projects with unclear scope or undefined success metrics.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item rv d1"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">Who owns the code and IP at the end of the engagement?</span><div class="faq-toggle">+</div></div><div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-a-inner">You own 100% of the code, IP, and all related assets from day one. Our standard agreements include full IP assignment clauses. We don't retain any licenses, rights, or "platform fees" on work we produce. The codebase is entirely yours — we just build it.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item rv d2"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">How do you handle confidentiality and security?</span><div class="faq-toggle">+</div></div><div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-a-inner">Every engineer signs a comprehensive NDA before any engagement begins. We're SOC 2 Type II compliant, operate with zero-trust access controls, and use hardware-enforced full-disk encryption on all developer machines. For financial and healthcare clients, we maintain dedicated audit trails and access logs for all code interactions.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item rv d2"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">What happens if we're not satisfied with the work?</span><div class="faq-toggle">+</div></div><div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-a-inner">We've never had a project end in dissatisfaction — but we take that risk seriously. Every engagement includes explicit quality milestones with mutual sign-off. If any milestone doesn't meet agreed standards, we rectify at our cost. We also offer a 2-week trial period on Embed engagements so you can evaluate fit before committing long-term.</p></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item rv d3"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">Do you provide ongoing maintenance after the project ends?</span><div class="faq-toggle">+</div></div><div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-a-inner">Yes. All Build engagements include 90 days of post-launch SRE coverage as standard. After that, we offer a Maintain retainer — typically 1–2 engineers on reduced hours — to handle updates, performance improvements, and incident response. Many clients roll directly from Build into an Embed or Maintain arrangement.</p></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(item=>{
  item.querySelector('.faq-q')?.addEventListener('click',()=>{
    const was=item.classList.contains('open');
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(i=>i.classList.remove('open'));
    if(!was)item.classList.add('open');
  });
});
</script>
